  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mechanical Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking an experienced <strong>Mechanical Engineer</strong> to help design and develop a <strong>precision manufacturing system for high-performance audio equipment</strong>.<br /></p><p>This is a <strong>contract role</strong> with the potential for <strong>long-term or full-time engagement</strong> based on performance and project needs.<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Design mechanical systems for precision manufacturing and assembly</p></li><li><p>Develop mechanisms involving tight tolerances, vibration control, and repeatability</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with electrical and industrial design counterparts</p></li><li><p>Produce manufacturable designs (CAD, drawings, BOMs)</p></li><li><p>Support prototyping, testing, and iteration</p></li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Strong background in mechanical engineering for <strong>precision or electromechanical systems</strong></p></li><li><p>Experience with <strong>manufacturing-oriented design</strong> (DFM/DFA)</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in professional CAD tools (SolidWorks, Fusion 360, Creo, or similar)</p></li><li><p>Understanding of materials, tolerances, and mechanical reliability</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working in a small, focused team with minimal oversight</p></li></ul><p><strong>Nice to Have</strong></p><ul><li><p>Experience with audio, acoustics, or vibration-sensitive systems</p></li><li><p>Background in CNC, tooling, or production equipment</p></li><li><p>Startup or early-stage product development experience</p></li></ul><p><strong>Engagement Details</strong></p><ul><li><p>Contract-based (scope and duration defined upfront)</p></li><li><p>Long-term hire potential for the right candidate</p></li></ul>",
